          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The energy  distribution  of  the  photoneutrons  was",
                " obtained  by (1) summing the neutrons in each energy",
                " interval over the angles 30,  50,  70,  90, 110, 130",
                " and  150  degrees,  (2) dividing the neutron sums by",
                " the sum of the fractional solid angles, (3) dividing",
                " by  the  number of moles of target irradiated by the",
                " beam and (4) dividing by the exposure in  roentgens,",
                " corrected  for the effective absorption of x-rays by",
                " the target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Arbitrary unit =",
                " 10**6* neutron/(0.5*MeV*mole*roentgen).",
                " The yield,    in    units    10**7    neutrons   per",
                " mole-roentgen,  was 1.4 with the error of  0.2.  The",
                " calculated   energy   distribution   which   gave  a",
                " satisfactory   correspondence   to   the    observed",
                " photoneutrons  consisted  of 90%  evaporation from a",
                " compound nucleus and 10%  emission by the  resonance",
                " direct effect."
              ]
            }
          ],
